"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-china-olympic-diving-roster-team-paris-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"China's Olympic diving roster for the Paris Games includes the reigning world champions in all eight events that are on the Olympic program.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 140, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 5, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9457817056413367, \"rank\": 0.05718285348116074, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China could become the first nation to sweep all eight gold medals at a single Olympics.\", \"from\": 142, \"to\": 230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 142, \"end\": 147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9457817056413367, \"rank\": 0.05718285348116074, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It won seven of the eight at the last two Games in Rio and Tokyo and six or seven golds at each of the last five Games.\", \"from\": 232, \"to\": 351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 283, \"end\": 286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999163265, \"rank\": 8.374693840174317e-11, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 291, \"end\": 296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9714282155482633, \"rank\": 0.029395569129056002, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Synchronized events were added starting with the 2000 Sydney Games, doubling the amount of Olympic diving events from four to eight.\", \"from\": 353, \"to\": 485, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The team announced Tuesdayincludes five returning gold medalists from the Tokyo Olympics: Xie Siyi (men's individual and synchro springboard), Wang Zongyuan (men's synchro springboard), Cao Yuan (men's platform), Quan Hongchan (women's platform) and Chen Yuxi (women's synchro platform).\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 577, \"end\": 585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xie_Siyi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Xie Siyi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xie_Siyi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xie_Siyi\"}, {\"begin\": 630, \"end\": 643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Zongyuan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wang Zongyuan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Zongyuan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Zongyuan\"}, {\"begin\": 673, \"end\": 681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Yuan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cao Yuan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Yuan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Yuan\"}, {\"begin\": 737, \"end\": 746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Yuxi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chen Yuxi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Yuxi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chen_Yuxi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The team returns all eight divers who won gold medals at this past February's world championships in events that are on the Olympic program.\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 916, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That includes Long Daoyi (men's synchro springboard), Yang Hao (men's individual and synchro platform), Lian Junjie (men's synchro platform), Chang Yani (women's individual and synchro springboard), Chen Yiwen (women's synchro springboard), plus Wang, Quan and Chen Yuxi.\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 1189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cao, 29, is the most experienced diver on the team.\", \"from\": 1191, \"to\": 1242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1191, \"end\": 1194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Cao\", \"score\": 0.9999999837671113, \"rank\": 1.6232984518942883e-08, \"text\": \"Cao\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Cao\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Cao\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has competed and won a medal at every Olympics and world championships dating to the 2012 London Games, save the 2023 Worlds.\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cao can tie the Chinese record of four Olympic diving appearances that is shared by Guo Jingjing, Wu Minxia and Xiong Ni, according to the OlyMADMen.\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1374, \"end\": 1377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Cao\", \"score\": 0.9999999837671113, \"rank\": 1.6232984518942883e-08, \"text\": \"Cao\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Cao\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cao_Cao\"}, {\"begin\": 1458, \"end\": 1470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guo_Jingjing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Guo Jingjing\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guo_Jingjing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guo_Jingjing\"}, {\"begin\": 1472, \"end\": 1481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wu_Minxia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wu Minxia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wu_Minxia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wu_Minxia\"}, {\"be